description: Translates : Cable & X-Force (2013) #12 , Uncanny X-Force (2013) #08 , X-Men Legacy (2013) #12-13 , Deadpool (2013) #10-12

Red Jack is back! London is gripped by terror as murder most foul is committed night after night. The culprit strikes as if invisible, leaving only the mutilated remains of his victims to show his passing. Scotland Yard is baffled and in desperation, calls in an American husband and wife team of detectives to solve the case of "Jack the Ripper." As the death toll mounts, the eccentric Americans discover a series of grisly clues leading into the highest reaches of British society - including the Royal Family! Softcover, 96 pages, B&W. Cover price $9.95.
name: Jack the Ripper

description: From the haunted heights of a mysterious castle to the dizzying depths of the deep seas, the Amazing Spider-Man must take on not one, not six, not twelve - but ninety-nine of the Marvel Universe's deadliest villains to save the lives of countless innocents! Trapped aboard a submarine, Spider-Man finds himself in a race against time - but things get worse when Spidey's ninety-nine problems give way to one big one: Kraven the Hunter! With innocent lives on the line, can Peter Parker outfox his mysterious captors to win his freedom? Matt Kindt (Mind MGMT) and Marco Rudy (Swamp Thing) bring you a defining hour in the life of the webbed wonder! Collecting MARVEL KNIGHTS: SPIDER-MAN (2013) #1-5.
name: TPB

description:
“Every saga has a beginning.”—Star Wars: Episode I the Phantom Menace

In this issue of Star Wars Insider, we bring you the 50 greatest reasons to love the Star Wars Prequels! Featuring a countdown of the ultimate moments from Star Wars Episodes I, II and III! Did everyone's favourite Gungan made the top 50? We have also go behind the scenes at Jabba's Palace with Bib Fortuna, plus all of your favourite regular features!

Issue highlights:

  • 50 greatest reasons to love Star Wars Prequels!
  • Camille Paglia on why Revenge of the Sith is an artistic triumph!
  • Actor Milton Johns on how he came to spend an awful long time on The Empire Strikes Back set!
  • We look at the amazing stop-motion work of Jon Berg!
  • Author Kevin J. Anderson on Jedi Academy, Young Jedi Knights, and more!
  • Brand-new tale from Edward Ederlac with art from Joe Corroney and Brian Miller!

Insider presents  the essential guide to the Empire’s deadliest soldiers!

In this issue of Star Wars Insider, the Empire strikes as bestselling Star Wars author Jason Fry investigates the Emperor’s loyal soldiers! Who are they? Where are they from? And what kind of strange varients of that famous and fearsome armor are there?

Issue highlights:

  • The essential guide to the Empire’s deadliest soldiers!
  • An all-new character is introduced in a spectacular new story!
  • Test your knowledge with our special Star Wars quiz!
  • Ralph McQuarrie - Visit Darth Vader’s secret mountain top castle!
